strings:
<se_low>King Trode: Hmm... How intriguing!
I never would have expected to find signs of other humans having been here!
<se_low>King Trode: Fascinating! Some places in the world are so peculiar they're almost beyond the comprehension of the average fellow.<page>King Trode: Not that I am in any way average, of course!
<se_high>Jessica: I wonder what it must've been like to live in such a secluded place? I'm sure I would've died from loneliness!

<se_low>Yangus: Cor, wot a view, eh!? I've always loved bein'
in 'igh places ever since I was a kid.
I feel like I was made for 'em!

<se_low>Yangus: Normally, when I tell people that, they give me this funny look...<page>Yangus: ...and mutter somefin' about it not bein' very likely that I'll ever be a man in an 'igh place.
Beats me why, though.
<se_def>Angelo: You'd never know all this was up here from down below, would you?
<se_low>King Trode: Hm... Why on earth would someone have gone to the trouble of putting such an important<->looking monument all the way up here?
<se_low>King Trode: Some places in the world are so peculiar they're almost beyond the comprehension of the average fellow.<page>King Trode: Not that I am in any way average, of course!
<se_high>Jessica: Do you think the people who built this climbed up here all by themselves?
<se_low>Yangus: Wot a view, eh!? I've always loved bein' in 'igh places ever since I was a kid.
<se_def>Angelo: You'd never know all this was up here from down below, would you?
<se_high>Red: Looks like it's been quite a while since people lived 'ere, eh? Wonder wot they were doin' 'ere...

<se_high>Red: Protectin' that monument, maybe?
It don't make no sense to me.
<se_low>Morrie: For me, I could never live here in this place. There is not enough PASSION! Not enough GUSTO!
<se_high>Red: There's signs o' life 'ere, but it ain't recent, that's for sure. An' that monument under the 'ouse is pretty weird, innit?
<se_high>Red: Is that wot the people 'ere were doin', is it? Lookin' after that monument? I s'pose we'll never know now...
<se_low>Morrie: For me, I could never live here in this place. There is not enough PASSION! Not enough GUSTO!
